-- Telstra's Split of Retail, Network Businesses Approved by Australia Senate
-- B y   G e m m a   D a l e y
-- 2010-11-26T01:45:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-26/telstra-s-split-of-retail-network-businesses-approved-by-australia-senate.html
Australia’s upper house Senate voted
to split Telstra Corp.’s retail business from its copper wire
network. The government needed to pass the laws to allow it to
build a A$35.7 billion ($35 billion) national high-speed
Internet network.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gemma Daley at 
 gdaley@bloomberg.net  